<subSubSection id="8D9386C89441FFEF1AB2FEF5FD59FEB6" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="C536D5439441FFEF1AB2FEF5FD59FEB6" blockId="8.[151,1437,290,820]" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis id="F7FD09519441FFEF1AB2FEF5FEC4FEEA" bold="true" box="[151,286,290,316]" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">Etymology.</emphasis>
The generic name is based on the latin “ 
<emphasis id="F7FD09519441FFEF18C2FEF4FCEAFEEA" box="[743,816,291,316]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">carina</emphasis>
” referring to its paired prosternal carinae and the name 
<taxonomicName id="0289AEC09441FFEF1AB2FE90FED6FEB6" authorityName="Li &amp; Kundrata &amp; Huang &amp; Cai" authorityYear="2022" box="[151,268,327,352]" class="Insecta" family="Artematopodidae" genus="Bipogonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F7FD09519441FFEF1AB2FE90FED6FEB6" box="[151,268,327,352]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">Bipogonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The name is feminine in gender.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8D9386C89441FFEF1AE2FEBEFE49FDC2" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="C536D5439441FFEF1AE2FEBEFE49FDC2" blockId="8.[151,1437,290,820]" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis id="F7FD09519441FFEF1AE2FEBEFE98FE55" bold="true" box="[199,322,361,387]" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Antennomeres distinctly serrate, less than twice as long as wide (
<figureCitation id="5DB2C9C69441FFEF1E70FEBDFB19FE52" box="[1109,1219,362,388]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1503,1527]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1480]" captionTargetId="figure-18@11.[151,1436,181,1480]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 10. Details of Carinibipogonia xiai Li, Kundrata &amp; Cai gen. et sp. nov., holotype, NIGP179432, under confocal microscopy. A, Head, ventral view. B, Prothorax, ventral view, showing the paired longitudinal ridges (arrowhead). C, Fore and mid legs. D, Elytral apex, showing the interlocking tongue (arrowhead). E, Abdominal apex, ventral view. F, Head, dorsal view. G, Antenna, dorsal view. H, Elytron, dorsal view. I, Ovipositor, dorsal view. Abbreviations: a1–11, antennomeres 1–11; cl, clypeus; gs, gonostylus; lbp, labial palp; md, mandible; mstb, mesotibia; msts, mesotarsus; mt, mentum; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; pts, protarsus; v5, ventrite 5. Scale bars: 300 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500952" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500952/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">Fig. 10G</figureCitation>
). Anterior edge of frontoclypeus dentate (
<figureCitation id="5DB2C9C69441FFEF1BB3FE59FE22FE7E" box="[406,504,398,424]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1503,1527]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1480]" captionTargetId="figure-18@11.[151,1436,181,1480]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 10. Details of Carinibipogonia xiai Li, Kundrata &amp; Cai gen. et sp. nov., holotype, NIGP179432, under confocal microscopy. A, Head, ventral view. B, Prothorax, ventral view, showing the paired longitudinal ridges (arrowhead). C, Fore and mid legs. D, Elytral apex, showing the interlocking tongue (arrowhead). E, Abdominal apex, ventral view. F, Head, dorsal view. G, Antenna, dorsal view. H, Elytron, dorsal view. I, Ovipositor, dorsal view. Abbreviations: a1–11, antennomeres 1–11; cl, clypeus; gs, gonostylus; lbp, labial palp; md, mandible; mstb, mesotibia; msts, mesotarsus; mt, mentum; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; pts, protarsus; v5, ventrite 5. Scale bars: 300 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500952" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500952/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">Fig. 10F</figureCitation>
). Mandibles with subapical tooth (
<figureCitation id="5DB2C9C69441FFEF1953FE59FC02FE7E" box="[886,984,398,424]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1503,1527]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1480]" captionTargetId="figure-18@11.[151,1436,181,1480]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 10. Details of Carinibipogonia xiai Li, Kundrata &amp; Cai gen. et sp. nov., holotype, NIGP179432, under confocal microscopy. A, Head, ventral view. B, Prothorax, ventral view, showing the paired longitudinal ridges (arrowhead). C, Fore and mid legs. D, Elytral apex, showing the interlocking tongue (arrowhead). E, Abdominal apex, ventral view. F, Head, dorsal view. G, Antenna, dorsal view. H, Elytron, dorsal view. I, Ovipositor, dorsal view. Abbreviations: a1–11, antennomeres 1–11; cl, clypeus; gs, gonostylus; lbp, labial palp; md, mandible; mstb, mesotibia; msts, mesotarsus; mt, mentum; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; pts, protarsus; v5, ventrite 5. Scale bars: 300 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500952" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500952/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">Fig. 10F</figureCitation>
). Apical maxillary palpomere not clearly expanded apically (
<figureCitation id="5DB2C9C69441FFEF1B54FE65FE2CFE1A" box="[369,502,434,460]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1503,1527]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1480]" captionTargetId="figure-18@11.[151,1436,181,1480]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 10. Details of Carinibipogonia xiai Li, Kundrata &amp; Cai gen. et sp. nov., holotype, NIGP179432, under confocal microscopy. A, Head, ventral view. B, Prothorax, ventral view, showing the paired longitudinal ridges (arrowhead). C, Fore and mid legs. D, Elytral apex, showing the interlocking tongue (arrowhead). E, Abdominal apex, ventral view. F, Head, dorsal view. G, Antenna, dorsal view. H, Elytron, dorsal view. I, Ovipositor, dorsal view. Abbreviations: a1–11, antennomeres 1–11; cl, clypeus; gs, gonostylus; lbp, labial palp; md, mandible; mstb, mesotibia; msts, mesotarsus; mt, mentum; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; pts, protarsus; v5, ventrite 5. Scale bars: 300 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500952" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500952/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">Fig. 10A, F</figureCitation>
). Prosternum in front of coxae with paired longitudinal ridges; ridges not extending to anterior half of prosternum (
<figureCitation id="5DB2C9C69441FFEF1824FE01FDB1FE26" box="[513,619,470,496]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1503,1527]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1480]" captionTargetId="figure-18@11.[151,1436,181,1480]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 10. Details of Carinibipogonia xiai Li, Kundrata &amp; Cai gen. et sp. nov., holotype, NIGP179432, under confocal microscopy. A, Head, ventral view. B, Prothorax, ventral view, showing the paired longitudinal ridges (arrowhead). C, Fore and mid legs. D, Elytral apex, showing the interlocking tongue (arrowhead). E, Abdominal apex, ventral view. F, Head, dorsal view. G, Antenna, dorsal view. H, Elytron, dorsal view. I, Ovipositor, dorsal view. Abbreviations: a1–11, antennomeres 1–11; cl, clypeus; gs, gonostylus; lbp, labial palp; md, mandible; mstb, mesotibia; msts, mesotarsus; mt, mentum; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; pts, protarsus; v5, ventrite 5. Scale bars: 300 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500952" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500952/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">Fig. 10B</figureCitation>
). Elytra with 10 puncture rows. Inner posterobasal angle of radial cell almost right (
<figureCitation id="5DB2C9C69441FFEF1B08FE2DFE5FFDC2" box="[301,389,506,532]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1322,1346]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1298]" captionTargetId="figure-22@10.[151,1436,181,1298]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 9. Details of Carinibipogonia xiai Li, Kundrata &amp; Cai gen. et sp. nov., holotype, NIGP179432, under widefield fluorescence. A, Head and prothorax, dorsal view. B, Head and prothorax, ventral view. C, Hind wing, dorsal view. D, Abdomen, ventral view. E, Elytron, ventral view.Abbreviations: an, antenna; el, elytron; lbp, labial palp; md, mandible; mt, mentum; mxp, maxillary palp; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; R, radial cell; v1–5, ventrites 1–5. Scale bars: 500 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500950" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500950/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">Fig. 9C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8D9386C89441FFEF1AE2FDCAFBECFDEE" box="[199,1078,541,568]" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" type="description">
<paragraph id="C536D5439441FFEF1AE2FDCAFBECFDEE" blockId="8.[151,1437,290,820]" box="[199,1078,541,568]" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis id="F7FD09519441FFEF1AE2FDCAFE83FDE1" bold="true" box="[199,345,541,567]" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">Description.</emphasis>
Since this genus is monotypic, see the species description below.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8D9386C89441FFEF1AE2FD95FB15FCE2" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C536D5439441FFEF1AE2FD95FB15FCE2" blockId="8.[151,1437,290,820]" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis id="F7FD09519441FFEF1AE2FD95FEE1FD8A" bold="true" box="[199,315,578,604]" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="0289AEC09441FFEF1B61FD95FE25FD8A" authority="Li &amp; Kundrata &amp; Huang &amp; Cai, 2022" authorityName="Li &amp; Kundrata &amp; Huang &amp; Cai" authorityYear="2022" box="[324,511,578,604]" class="Insecta" family="Artematopodidae" genus="Carinibipogonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="F7FD09519441FFEF1B61FD95FE25FD8A" box="[324,511,578,604]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">Carinibipogonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="F7FD09519441FFEF1822FD95FDABFD8A" bold="true" box="[519,625,578,604]" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="ECCEB42A9441FFEF1822FD95FDABFD8A" box="[519,625,578,604]" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is generally very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="0289AEC09441FFEF1991FD94FBF3FD8A" authority="Both" authorityName="Li &amp; Kundrata &amp; Huang &amp; Cai" authorityYear="2022" box="[948,1065,579,604]" class="Insecta" family="Artematopodidae" genus="Bipogonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="F7FD09519441FFEF1991FD94FBF3FD8A" box="[948,1065,579,604]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">Bipogonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="F7FD09519441FFEF1E14FD95FB46FD8A" bold="true" box="[1073,1180,578,604]" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="ECCEB42A9441FFEF1E14FD95FB46FD8A" box="[1073,1180,578,604]" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
Both genera share the anteriorly dentate frontoclypeus, strongly serrate antennae, and mandibles with a subapical tooth. The only major difference between them appears to be the presence of paired prosternal ridges in 
<taxonomicName id="0289AEC09441FFEF1E14FD5DFB36FD72" authorityName="Li &amp; Kundrata &amp; Huang &amp; Cai" authorityYear="2022" box="[1073,1260,650,676]" class="Insecta" family="Artematopodidae" genus="Carinibipogonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F7FD09519441FFEF1E14FD5DFB36FD72" box="[1073,1260,650,676]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">Carinibipogonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The prosternal ridges generally extend to the anterior margin of prosternum in other artematopodids with prosternal ridges. However, in 
<taxonomicName id="0289AEC09441FFEF1A93FD05FEABFD3A" authorityName="Li &amp; Kundrata &amp; Huang &amp; Cai" authorityYear="2022" box="[182,369,722,748]" class="Insecta" family="Artematopodidae" genus="Carinibipogonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F7FD09519441FFEF1A93FD05FEABFD3A" box="[182,369,722,748]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">Carinibipogonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the ridges disappear in the anterior half of prosternum. 
<taxonomicName id="0289AEC09441FFEF19DCFD05FB3DFD3A" authority="Li &amp; Kundrata &amp; Huang &amp; Cai, 2022" authorityName="Li &amp; Kundrata &amp; Huang &amp; Cai" authorityYear="2022" box="[1017,1255,722,748]" class="Insecta" family="Artematopodidae" genus="Carinibipogonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xiai" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="F7FD09519441FFEF19DCFD05FB3DFD3A" box="[1017,1255,722,748]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">Carinibipogonia xiai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="F7FD09519441FFEF1ED5FD05FA91FD3A" bold="true" box="[1264,1355,722,748]" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="ECCEB42A9441FFEF1ED5FD05FA91FD3A" box="[1264,1355,722,748]" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="0289AEC09441FFEF1AF0FD20FEEAFCC6" authority="Li &amp; Kundrata &amp; Huang &amp; Cai, 2022" authorityName="Li &amp; Kundrata &amp; Huang &amp; Cai" authorityYear="2022" box="[213,304,758,784]" class="Insecta" family="Artematopodidae" genus="Bipogonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fortis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="F7FD09519441FFEF1AF0FD20FEEAFCC6" box="[213,304,758,784]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">B. fortis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="F7FD09519441FFEF1B1DFD21FE48FCC6" bold="true" box="[312,402,758,784]" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="ECCEB42A9441FFEF1B1DFD21FE48FCC6" box="[312,402,758,784]" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
additionally in having a more elongated radial cell. However, this character state cannot be observed in 
<taxonomicName id="0289AEC09441FFEF1B05FCCCFE4CFCE2" authority="Li &amp; Kundrata &amp; Huang &amp; Cai, 2022" authorityName="Li &amp; Kundrata &amp; Huang &amp; Cai" authorityYear="2022" box="[288,406,794,820]" class="Insecta" family="Artematopodidae" genus="Bipogonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trivialis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="F7FD09519441FFEF1B05FCCCFE4CFCE2" box="[288,406,794,820]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">B. trivialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="F7FD09519441FFEF1BB8FCCDFE2DFCE2" bold="true" box="[413,503,794,820]" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="ECCEB42A9441FFEF1BB8FCCDFE2DFCE2" box="[413,503,794,820]" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
since the hind wings are not exposed in the available specimens.
</paragraph>
